#8988

```suggestion
Copyright (c) 2024 Jireh Loreaux. All rights reserved.
```
and the authors line
A vague justification for this in a comment would be nice; otherwise it's harder to review a PR in future that removes it.
Sorry, I'm not sure what justification would look like beyond "that notion is not needed to define this notion", and in any case the way to review a PR that removes it is to say "no". :-)
@semorrison, I think you can claim this file thanks to leanprover-community/mathlib#4686
Sure. I've been (and plan to continue!) to just copy and paste the header from whichever file I am splitting out of, but have no objections if others want to do the forensic work. :-)
Oh, I guess in this one I didn't and just made a new one for some very small files.
